canonical:
  title: 太后上同前表
  author: 李穀
  language: lzh
  text: 母儀丕顯於東朝曾崇徽號婦順肇形於內治新布德音縟禮畢陳慈風遠被云云靜深照物冲澹怡神贊先帝之睿謨更張大化毓吾皇之聖德馴致隆平慶洽中闈歡騰諸夏云云幸叨近列夙荷洪私旣廣至仁式敍六官之政願輸微懇對敭萬歲之休
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 太后上同前表
  author: 李穀
  language: lzh
  text: 母儀丕顯於東朝。曾崇徽號。婦順肇形於內治。新布德音。縟禮畢陳。慈風遠被。云云。靜深照物。冲澹怡神。贊先帝之睿謨。更張大化。毓吾皇之聖德。馴致隆平。慶洽中闈。歡騰諸夏。云云。幸叨近列。夙荷洪私。旣廣至仁。式敍六官之政。願輸微懇。對敭萬歲之休。
korean:
  title: 태후상동전 표
  author: 이곡
  language: kor
  text: 모의(母儀)가 크게 동조(東朝)에 나타나시어 일찍 휘호(徽號)를 높이셨고, 부덕(婦德)이 진작 내치(內治)에 드러나 새로 덕음(德音)을 반포하시어 화려한 예식을 모두 거행하니 인자하신 풍화(風化)가 멀리 퍼지옵나이다. 운운.고요하고 깊으심으로 사물을 비추시고 충담(沖澹)으로 심신(心神)을 즐기사, 선제(先帝)의 예모(睿謨)를 협찬(協贊)하여 큰 교화를 경장(更張)하시고, 오황(吾皇)의 성덕(聖德)을 기르사 태평을 순치(馴致)하시니 경사가 궁중에 흡족하고 환성(歡聲)이 제하(諸夏)에 비등(沸騰)하옵나이다. 운운. 다행히 근신(近臣)의 반열(班列)에 끼어 진작 홍은(洪恩)을 입어왔사오니 이미 지극한 인(仁)을 넓혀 육궁(六宮)의 정사를 펴시는 이때, 작은 정성을 받들어 만세(萬歲)의 성수(聖壽)를 대양(對敭)하고자 하나이다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0350_010_0140&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Memorial Presented to the Queen Dowager
  author: Lee Gok
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Your maternal virtue shines brilliantly in the Eastern Palace,
    Early honored with gracious titles of respect.
    Your wifely grace manifests in the inner governance,
    Newly proclaiming virtuous edicts.
    Ceremonies elaborate and complete unfold,
    As compassionate influence spreads far and wide.

    With stillness profound, you illuminate all things,
    With serene emptiness, you nurture the spirit.
    You assist the late Emperor's wise counsel,
    Bringing greater transformation to the realm.
    You cultivate our sovereign's sacred virtue,
    Leading all toward an age of perfect peace.
    Blessing fills the palace chambers,
    Joy resounds throughout the land.

    Humble fortune grants me place among your near servants,
    Long have I received your boundless grace.
    Now that you extend your supreme benevolence,
    Ordering the affairs of the Six Ministries,
    I offer my meager devotion,
    That I may acclaim ten thousand years of your noble longevity.
  footnotes:
    - This is a ceremonial memorial composed to celebrate the achievements and virtues of a Queen Dowager (likely during the Goryeo period). The 'Eastern Palace' refers to the traditional seat of the Queen Dowager. The 'Six Ministries' refer to the traditional administrative divisions of Korean government.
    - The repetition of 'yungun' (云云, 'and so forth') in the original serves as a rhetorical device indicating the abundance of virtues being praised.
